dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] East Retford, solid and drift, sheet 101
dc_description_s: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 101 solid and drift. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 53.416700. South Decimal Degree 53.2500. East Decimal Degree -0.7500. West Decimal Degree -1.1833. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of Great Britain. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Original Geological Survey on the one-inch scale by W.T. Aveline et al. Published hand-coloured on Old Series sheets 82 N.E. (1861 revised 1875, additions 1897), 82 S.E. (1858) and 83 (1886). Surveyed on six-inch scale by E.G. Smith et al. in 1941-1961.".
dc_publisher_s: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1967.
